<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Hamburger</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 pound ground beef (80% lean)</li>
            <li>Salt and black pepper to taste</li>
            <li>4 hamburger buns</li>
            <li>Lettuce leaves</li>
            <li>Sliced tomatoes</li>
            <li>Sliced red onion</li>
            <li>Pickle slices</li>
            <li>Ketchup, mustard, and mayonnaise for condiments</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>lunch</li>
            <li>grilling</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Divide the ground beef into 4 equal portions and shape them into burger patties. Season each patty with salt and black pepper.</li>
            <li>Preheat a grill or skillet over medium-high heat. Cook the burger patties for 3-4 minutes per side or until they reach your desired level of doneness.</li>
            <li>Toast the hamburger buns on the grill or in a toaster until lightly golden.</li>
            <li>Assemble the hamburgers by placing a lettuce leaf on the bottom half of each bun. Top with a cooked patty and add sliced tomatoes, red onion, and pickles.</li>
            <li>Spread ketchup, mustard, and mayonnaise on the top half of the buns. Place the top bun over the toppings to complete the hamburgers.</li>
            <li>Serve the hamburgers hot and enjoy!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

